Cysteine 910 and cysteine 912

6j8e C 55 A 910

A redox-regulated disulphide may form between Sodium channel subunit beta-2 and Sodium channel protein type 2 subunit alpha at these cysteines.

6j8e C 55 A 912

A redox-regulated disulphide may form between Sodium channel subunit beta-2 and Sodium channel protein type 2 subunit alpha at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.
